cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer-aided detection in digital mammography exams, which involves image analysis and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses transfer learning and deep learning models, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of adversarial learning is also mentioned, which is a technique commonly used in generative models and could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of annotations and class imbalance, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
